  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; seven carry explicitly-low confidence scores or wide uncertainty bounds that are documented honestly with full rationale. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Decision: Accepted with documented offset rationale for the one factor where achievedLevel equals requiredLevel only after accounting for compensating evidence from sensitivity analysis. No weakener should fire on this package.",
