      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is used. Explicitly-low confidence flag: the model is known to have limited accuracy for shear histories below 50 Pa (literature R² ~0.65 in that regime). The sensitivity analysis shows that 78% of the predicted hemolysis accumulates above 50 Pa shear, where model accuracy is higher (R² ~0.88). The sub-50 Pa regime contribution is documented with a 35% uncertainty bound and contributes 22% of total hemolysis variance.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
