      "rationale": "All 12 uncertain model inputs are characterised with literature-derived or experimentally-derived distributions. Explicitly-low confidence on power-law exponent C (CV 15%) and RBC fragility scalar (CV 18%): both are sourced from literature meta-analyses with high inter-study variability. Distributions are documented with source references, and both parameters are identified as primary variance drivers in the sensitivity analysis. Targeted experimental characterisation of C is recommended as a future action but is not required for the current decision given the conservative over-prediction bias.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
